An example element with large padding, border and margin.
\f[CR]offsetHeight\f[R] is the layout height of the element including
its padding and border, and excluding its margin.
.PP
The example image above shows a scrollbar and an \f[CR]offsetHeight\f[R]
which fits on the window.
However, non\-scrollable elements may have large \f[CR]offsetHeight\f[R]
values, much larger than the visible content.
These elements are typically contained within scrollable elements;
consequently, these non\-scrollable elements may be completely or partly
invisible, depending on the \f[CR]scrollTop\f[R] setting of the
scrollable container.
